  text: Use this formula in Excel:

`=IF(I12="","",I12)`

This makes `J23`:
- show the same value as `I12` when `I12` has something in it
- stay truly blank when `I12` is blank

Why your current formula failed:
- `IF(I12="","")` is incomplete because it only gives the value-if-blank part.
- Excel then interprets the missing third argument unexpectedly, which can lead to `FALSE`.
- If the cell is formatted as a date and the result is effectively zero/empty in some cases, Excel may display `01/01/1900`.

